==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flapjack
<hw>Flap"jack`</hw> <pr>(fl⟦acr⟧p"j⟦acr⟧k`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A flat cake turned on the griddle while cooking; a
griddlecake or pancake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A fried dough cake containing fruit; a
turnover.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flap-mouthed</ent>⟦br⟧
